---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base title="About — Agent Native Engineering" description="What this site is, who writes it, and the rule that every claim ships with a source.">
  <div class="wrap" data-r="pad">
    <article class="article">
      <a class="backlink" href="/">← Home</a>
      <header style="margin:22px 0 0">
        <div class="eyebrow">// ABOUT</div>
        <h1 class="page-h1" data-r="page-h1" style="margin-top:14px">About</h1>
      </header>
      <div class="prose" style="margin-top:30px">
        <p>
          <strong>Agent Native Engineering</strong> is open knowledge for building, operating, and
          engineering with AI agents in production — agents that work under real load, not bolt-ons
          and not demos.
        </p>
        <p>
          The centre of the project is the <a href="/guide/">Field Guide</a> — twelve engineering domains,
          from scope and model selection through durable execution and security to evaluation and
          harness engineering, each grounded in real-world examples and studies rather than opinion.
          Around it sit <a href="/field-notes/">Daily Notes</a> from the work, a
          <a href="/architectures/">Reference Architecture</a> composed from open-source systems, and
          the <a href="/daily-brief/">Daily Brief</a> — a spoken digest of the notes.
        </p>
        <p>
          One rule holds the whole thing together: <strong>every claim ships with a source.</strong>
          The examples are real, cited, and linked. If we can't source it, we don't say it.
        </p>
        <h2>How this site is made</h2>
        <p>
          It dogfoods the premise. A scheduled agent drafts each day's note from real engineering
          work and opens a pull request; a human edits and merges. The site you're reading is, quite
          literally, built by agents and edited by a person — which is the whole point.
        </p>
        <p>
          Find the source and follow along at
          <a href="https://github.com/agentnativeengineering">github.com/agentnativeengineering</a>,
          or subscribe via <a href="/rss.xml">RSS</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>

  <Footer slot="footer" variant="slim" left={'About · <span class="strong">Agent Native Engineering</span> · CC BY 4.0'} />
</Base>
